• Put the avocados in a food processor and puree until smooth. Add the soy milk, cilantro, ginger, lemon juice, chili sauce, and salt. Process until smooth. • With the machine running, pour the yogurt and stock through the feed tube. • Transfer to a resealable container and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled. • Transfer the soup into serving bowls and place a little chopped bell pepper in the center. Serve immediately.